1
00:00:01,568 --> 00:00:03,235
Julia:
<i>Chester's mill is a place</i>
<i>like any other.</i>

2
00:00:03,237 --> 00:00:05,237
<i>At least it used to be</i>

3
00:00:05,239 --> 00:00:07,239
<i>Until we were cut off</i>
<i>from the rest of the world</i>

4
00:00:07,241 --> 00:00:09,108
<i>By a mysterious dome.</i>

5
00:00:12,680 --> 00:00:15,347
<i>Invisible, indestructible,</i>

6
00:00:15,349 --> 00:00:17,116
<i>Inescapable.</i>

7
00:00:17,118 --> 00:00:19,118
We're trapped.

8
00:00:19,120 --> 00:00:21,620
Julia:
<i>We don't know where it</i>
<i>came from or why it's here,</i>

9
00:00:21,622 --> 00:00:24,089
<i>But now that we're all trapped</i>
<i>under the dome together,</i>

10
00:00:24,091 --> 00:00:26,759
<i>None of our secrets are safe.</i>

11
00:00:26,761 --> 00:00:28,560
Dale barbara stands accused

12
00:00:28,562 --> 00:00:30,195
Of the attempted murder
of julia shumway.

13
00:00:30,197 --> 00:00:31,563
<i>And for the murders</i>

14
00:00:31,565 --> 00:00:34,199
<i>Of maxine and agatha seagrave.</i>

15
00:00:34,201 --> 00:00:36,435
I am not turning our town
into a police state

16
00:00:36,437 --> 00:00:38,237
Just because you say so.

17
00:00:38,239 --> 00:00:40,272
Big jim:
<i>It's not me, linda,</i>
<i>it's the people.</i>

18
00:00:40,274 --> 00:00:44,343
One drone caught surveillance
of this rennie murdering

19
00:00:44,345 --> 00:00:46,311
The town reverend
at the bridge roadblock.

20
00:00:46,313 --> 00:00:48,280
Big jim:
<i>That dome can't come down.</i>

21
00:00:48,282 --> 00:00:49,181
Not now.

22
00:00:49,183 --> 00:00:50,382
You're a sick bastard.

23
00:00:50,384 --> 00:00:53,318
Everyone's gonna
smile when you die.

24
00:00:54,387 --> 00:00:55,621
Phil:
<i>Why'd he do it?</i>

25
00:00:55,623 --> 00:00:57,389
Barbie won't
get away with it.

26
00:00:57,391 --> 00:00:59,458
Big jim:
To the charges brought
against you, how do you plead?

27
00:00:59,460 --> 00:01:00,826
Not guilty.

28
00:01:03,496 --> 00:01:05,330
Norrie:
It's the pink stars.

29
00:01:05,332 --> 00:01:06,365
What does it mean?

30
00:01:06,367 --> 00:01:07,733
Joe:
The egg.

31
00:01:07,735 --> 00:01:08,801
We think it's the source
that powers the whole dome.

32
00:01:08,803 --> 00:01:10,569
Angie:
<i>Do you trust your dad?</i>

33
00:01:10,571 --> 00:01:12,237
Of course I do.
You didn't always.

34
00:01:12,239 --> 00:01:15,207
<i>We all saw the same vision</i>
<i>at the dome, junior.</i>

35
00:01:15,209 --> 00:01:16,508
<i>Big jim has to die.</i>

36
00:01:16,510 --> 00:01:17,843
Norrie:
When the butterfly hatches...

37
00:01:17,845 --> 00:01:19,411
The monarch will be crowned.

38
00:01:38,131 --> 00:01:39,465
Hey, bud.

39
00:01:39,467 --> 00:01:41,733
We've been waiting on you.

40
00:01:41,735 --> 00:01:43,402
It's really happening.

41
00:01:43,404 --> 00:01:44,269
What's happening?

42
00:01:45,505 --> 00:01:46,371
Move away.

43
00:01:46,373 --> 00:01:48,373
Linda...
Back away!

44
00:01:48,375 --> 00:01:50,342
How long have you guys
known about this?

45
00:01:51,644 --> 00:01:52,578
What about you?

46
00:01:52,580 --> 00:01:54,546
Just a couple days, but, linda,

47
00:01:54,548 --> 00:01:55,681
Don't do anything rash.

48
00:01:55,683 --> 00:01:57,649
The kids-- they,

49
00:01:57,651 --> 00:01:59,585
They think the egg
is the source.

50
00:01:59,587 --> 00:02:01,220
Source of what?

51
00:02:01,222 --> 00:02:03,122
The dome.

52
00:02:04,224 --> 00:02:05,524
It's the generator of the dome.

53
00:02:05,526 --> 00:02:07,292
Norrie:
We can sort of talk to it.

54
00:02:07,294 --> 00:02:08,861
It told us
"the monarch will be crowned."

55
00:02:08,863 --> 00:02:10,295
What is that supposed to mean?

56
00:02:10,297 --> 00:02:11,630
Joe:
We don't know yet.

57
00:02:11,632 --> 00:02:13,132
But that's a monarch butterfly.

58
00:02:13,134 --> 00:02:14,833
We think it's got
to be important,

59
00:02:14,835 --> 00:02:17,269
So we have to get it out of
there before it hurts itself.

60
00:02:17,271 --> 00:02:18,370
Or worse.

61
00:02:18,372 --> 00:02:20,506
I know how it all sounds.

62
00:02:20,508 --> 00:02:23,609
But I believe them.

63
00:02:28,148 --> 00:02:29,515
Not guilty?

64
00:02:29,517 --> 00:02:30,749
What, are you insane?

65
00:02:30,751 --> 00:02:31,717
You think this is
some sort of game?

66
00:02:36,756 --> 00:02:38,657
You're the one
rolling the dice here

67
00:02:38,659 --> 00:02:40,592
'cause julia's still
out there somewhere.

68
00:02:40,594 --> 00:02:42,694
And she knows the truth.

69
00:02:42,696 --> 00:02:45,230
I already told people
the truth.

70
00:02:45,232 --> 00:02:46,498
You killed max,

71
00:02:46,500 --> 00:02:48,333
Her mother, and her bodyguard.

72
00:02:48,335 --> 00:02:51,436
Nobody can change that now.

73
00:02:51,438 --> 00:02:53,639
We'll see.

74
00:02:54,607 --> 00:02:56,542
You entered your plea.

75
00:02:56,544 --> 00:02:58,610
Now you get your justice.

76
00:03:05,652 --> 00:03:07,719
♪

77
00:03:11,691 --> 00:03:13,392
Tell me!

78
00:03:16,696 --> 00:03:18,830
Why do you want me
to kill my father?

79
00:03:23,537 --> 00:03:25,237
Hey, take it easy, julia.

80
00:03:25,239 --> 00:03:27,439
I appreciate everything
that you've done,

81
00:03:27,441 --> 00:03:28,674
But I can't hide out down here.

82
00:03:28,676 --> 00:03:30,709
You are not safe out
in the open.

83
00:03:30,711 --> 00:03:32,578
I'm the only one
who can exonerate barbie.

84
00:03:32,580 --> 00:03:34,446
Which is exactly why big jim
will have you killed

85
00:03:34,448 --> 00:03:35,847
Long before you can tell anyone.

86
00:03:35,849 --> 00:03:38,984
Then I'll die trying.

87
00:03:40,721 --> 00:03:41,820
Angie, please.

88
00:03:41,822 --> 00:03:43,555
You don't have
to come with me,

89
00:03:43,557 --> 00:03:45,691
But you can't stand
in my way.

90
00:03:52,599 --> 00:03:53,599
You don't know
anything about this.

91
00:03:53,601 --> 00:03:54,900
I mean, it could
be radioactive.

92
00:03:54,902 --> 00:03:56,001
The big dome isn't.

93
00:03:56,003 --> 00:03:58,437
Well, this doesn't
belong to you.

94
00:03:58,439 --> 00:04:00,505
As of now, this is
police property.

95
00:04:02,709 --> 00:04:04,776
What the hell?

96
00:04:09,816 --> 00:04:11,783
Barbie:
<i>You didn't think</i>

97
00:04:11,785 --> 00:04:13,685
I was just gonna roll over,
did you?

98
00:04:13,687 --> 00:04:15,621
Make this easy for you?

99
00:04:15,623 --> 00:04:17,289
No, nothing with you is easy.

100
00:04:17,291 --> 00:04:19,358
I know you're just gonna
screw me in the end.

101
00:04:19,360 --> 00:04:21,693
You don't know any other way.

102
00:04:21,695 --> 00:04:24,563
But at least
I can take you down with me.

103
00:04:26,834 --> 00:04:29,701
I don't think you understand
what's happening here.

104
00:04:29,703 --> 00:04:31,570
I could end this right now
with a bullet in your head.

105
00:04:31,572 --> 00:04:32,571
Oh, yeah.

106
00:04:32,573 --> 00:04:35,574
You can.

107
00:04:35,576 --> 00:04:36,742
But you won't.

108
00:04:36,744 --> 00:04:38,744
You won't

109
00:04:38,746 --> 00:04:40,612
Because there's
no audience here.

110
00:04:42,749 --> 00:04:45,517
The butterfly hits the dome.

111
00:04:45,519 --> 00:04:47,586
And makes some kind of spot.

112
00:04:48,655 --> 00:04:49,721
Oh, my god.

113
00:04:52,792 --> 00:04:54,860
Joe:
We've got to
do something.

114
00:05:01,467 --> 00:05:03,001
Guys?

115
00:05:05,505 --> 00:05:08,373
Is it just me or is it getting
crazy dark outside?

116
00:05:09,509 --> 00:05:10,809
Barbie:
<i>Listen, jim.</i>

117
00:05:10,811 --> 00:05:12,544
This isn't just
about killing me.

118
00:05:12,546 --> 00:05:14,012
This is about making sure

119
00:05:14,014 --> 00:05:16,048
This entire town knows
that you are judge,

120
00:05:16,050 --> 00:05:18,984
Jury and executioner.

121
00:05:49,816 --> 00:05:52,484
What the hell?

122
00:06:02,462 --> 00:06:04,096
What are you trying to tell me?!

123
00:06:23,116 --> 00:06:25,851
This is seriously
weirding me out.

124
00:06:25,853 --> 00:06:27,152
It's the middle of the day,

125
00:06:27,154 --> 00:06:29,921
But it looks like
it's midnight out there.

126
00:06:29,923 --> 00:06:30,989
There's no moon.

127
00:06:30,991 --> 00:06:32,858
No stars.

128
00:06:38,164 --> 00:06:39,898
It's dying, norrie.

129
00:06:41,934 --> 00:06:43,034
See?

130
00:06:43,036 --> 00:06:45,003
The dome's trying
to talk to us.

131
00:06:45,005 --> 00:06:46,671
Maybe it's some kind of warning.

132
00:06:46,673 --> 00:06:48,774
The dome's telling us we
have to get the butterfly

133
00:06:48,776 --> 00:06:50,008
Out of there before it dies.

134
00:06:50,010 --> 00:06:51,176
But we need the others.

135
00:06:51,178 --> 00:06:52,477
All right, I've heard enough.

136
00:06:52,479 --> 00:06:53,979
All available units?
Don't do this.

137
00:06:53,981 --> 00:06:55,414
All available units

138
00:06:55,416 --> 00:06:57,549
To ben drake's house.
Listen to them.

139
00:06:57,551 --> 00:06:58,750
Please.

140
00:06:58,752 --> 00:07:00,118
I found another dome.

141
00:07:00,120 --> 00:07:02,654
And some sort of... Egg.

142
00:07:02,656 --> 00:07:03,822
We're in trouble.

143
00:07:03,824 --> 00:07:06,158
Linda?

144
00:07:06,160 --> 00:07:07,793
It-it's the dome.

145
00:07:07,795 --> 00:07:08,827
It's all black.

146
00:07:08,829 --> 00:07:09,828
I know, junior.

147
00:07:09,830 --> 00:07:11,897
Just get your ass over here.

148
00:07:13,766 --> 00:07:15,634
All right,
I'm impounding this... Thing

149
00:07:15,636 --> 00:07:17,736
Until we see what happens.

150
00:07:17,738 --> 00:07:18,837
Linda, you found it?

151
00:07:18,839 --> 00:07:21,039
Jim, you need to see this.

152
00:07:21,041 --> 00:07:23,775
10-4. I'm on my way, too.

153
00:07:28,449 --> 00:07:29,848
Make it stop!
Norrie: We don't know how.

154
00:07:29,850 --> 00:07:31,850
Yeah, we-we kind of do.

155
00:07:31,852 --> 00:07:33,685
Remember?

156
00:07:34,754 --> 00:07:36,555
Oh, yeah.

157
00:07:36,557 --> 00:07:37,956
That time we touched it.

158
00:07:43,129 --> 00:07:44,963
No, I told you.

159
00:07:44,965 --> 00:07:46,465
This is police property now.

160
00:07:46,467 --> 00:07:47,499
If anybody's gonna touch it,

161
00:07:47,501 --> 00:07:48,733
It's gonna be me.

162
00:08:09,856 --> 00:08:10,822
We have to get to that egg.

163
00:08:10,824 --> 00:08:11,857
And we will.

164
00:08:11,859 --> 00:08:12,958
After we help barbie.

165
00:08:12,960 --> 00:08:14,259
No, it can't wait, julia.

166
00:08:14,261 --> 00:08:15,760
If linda takes
the mini-dome,

167
00:08:15,762 --> 00:08:17,062
And it ends up in
the wrong hands...

168
00:08:17,064 --> 00:08:18,163
Barbie needs my help.

169
00:08:18,165 --> 00:08:19,231
Our help.

170
00:08:19,233 --> 00:08:19,998
This might be
our only shot

171
00:08:20,000 --> 00:08:20,999
To save his life.

172
00:08:21,001 --> 00:08:22,767
Are you with me?

173
00:08:32,979 --> 00:08:34,646
She'll be fine.

174
00:08:34,648 --> 00:08:35,914
Joe:
It was the only way.

175
00:08:35,916 --> 00:08:37,015
So, now what?

176
00:08:38,584 --> 00:08:39,918
What did you guys do?

177
00:08:39,920 --> 00:08:41,052
Carolyn:
She touched the dome.

178
00:08:41,054 --> 00:08:42,888
Joe:
She got zapped.

179
00:08:42,890 --> 00:08:44,222
Like dodee.

180
00:08:44,224 --> 00:08:45,223
The monarch is
dying, junior.

181
00:08:45,225 --> 00:08:46,892
We need angie.
Screw angie.

182
00:08:46,894 --> 00:08:48,994
What?
She ran off
with julia.

183
00:08:48,996 --> 00:08:50,595
Julia was
under police protection.

184
00:08:50,597 --> 00:08:51,830
My protection.

185
00:08:51,832 --> 00:08:52,831
She did what
she had to do.

186
00:08:52,833 --> 00:08:53,865
By helping barbie?

187
00:08:53,867 --> 00:08:55,066
He shot julia.

188
00:08:55,068 --> 00:08:56,768
No, I saw him save her life.

189
00:08:58,638 --> 00:08:59,571
Things are
happening, junior.

190
00:08:59,573 --> 00:09:01,106
Things bigger than us.

191
00:09:01,108 --> 00:09:02,641
It's not always about you.

192
00:09:02,643 --> 00:09:03,675
Ben:
Guys!

193
00:09:03,677 --> 00:09:05,310
It's big jim.

194
00:09:05,312 --> 00:09:07,679
Norrie: Mom, you have
to get out of here.

195
00:09:07,681 --> 00:09:08,680
You, too, ben.

196
00:09:08,682 --> 00:09:09,681
This is on us.

197
00:09:09,683 --> 00:09:10,682
All three of us.

198
00:09:10,684 --> 00:09:12,250
Right, junior?

199
00:09:12,252 --> 00:09:13,718
Or do you want your dad
to lock that thing away

200
00:09:13,720 --> 00:09:15,253
Before it can give
us any answers?

201
00:09:19,559 --> 00:09:21,626
Let's go.

202
00:09:25,565 --> 00:09:27,732
I guess everyone is out
dealing with the blackout.

203
00:09:29,635 --> 00:09:31,836
Permanent darkness has
its bright side.

204
00:09:31,838 --> 00:09:33,838
Okay, the cells
are down there.

205
00:09:33,840 --> 00:09:36,308
I'll get the keys.

206
00:09:53,025 --> 00:09:55,594
My god, how are
you even standing?

207
00:09:55,596 --> 00:09:57,862
I don't know.

208
00:09:57,864 --> 00:10:01,800
But something out there really
wanted me back on my feet.

209
00:10:06,138 --> 00:10:07,872
All right, that's
enough, lovebirds.

210
00:10:07,874 --> 00:10:09,908
It's go time.

211
00:10:14,213 --> 00:10:15,814
Linda!

212
00:10:15,816 --> 00:10:17,749
Linda!
Jim...

213
00:10:17,751 --> 00:10:18,750
Linda!

214
00:10:18,752 --> 00:10:19,818
Are you okay?

215
00:10:19,820 --> 00:10:21,753
What happened? Where is it?

216
00:10:22,723 --> 00:10:24,322
Linda:
I don't know.

217
00:10:24,324 --> 00:10:26,691
But the egg...

218
00:10:26,693 --> 00:10:29,127
They think
it's the generator.

219
00:10:29,129 --> 00:10:31,296
That it might be able
to bring the whole dome down.

220
00:10:31,298 --> 00:10:33,064
Jim, we have
to find it.

221
00:10:33,066 --> 00:10:34,899
This could be our best shot
of getting out of here.

222
00:10:43,242 --> 00:10:45,076
Norrie:
Now all we have
to do is get angie.

223
00:10:45,078 --> 00:10:46,678
We don't even know
where she is.

224
00:10:46,680 --> 00:10:47,646
I know how
to find her.

225
00:10:47,648 --> 00:10:49,114
You do?

226
00:10:49,116 --> 00:10:50,949
She has a police radio.

227
00:10:50,951 --> 00:10:52,350
She stole one.

228
00:10:52,352 --> 00:10:54,653
We could send her a message.
For the entire force

229
00:10:54,655 --> 00:10:56,855
To hear? What can we even say?

230
00:11:01,094 --> 00:11:02,694
Oh, hell, no.

231
00:11:14,707 --> 00:11:16,408
Don't.

232
00:11:22,715 --> 00:11:24,683
No handcuff keys.

233
00:11:24,685 --> 00:11:26,017
Barbie:
Forget about it,
let's get out of here.

234
00:11:26,019 --> 00:11:28,687
You lose
something?

235
00:11:28,689 --> 00:11:29,888
Hold onto those
for me, will you?

236
00:11:29,890 --> 00:11:32,090
Joe:
Angie.

237
00:11:32,092 --> 00:11:33,825
Angie mcalister!

238
00:11:33,827 --> 00:11:34,959
Angie, if you can hear me,
look...

239
00:11:34,961 --> 00:11:37,162
We're on the move...

240
00:11:37,164 --> 00:11:38,930
With the mini-dome.

241
00:11:40,800 --> 00:11:42,834
Remember where we went to hide

242
00:11:42,836 --> 00:11:44,069
When we broke mom's old mirror?

243
00:11:44,071 --> 00:11:45,904
Meet us there.

244
00:11:52,812 --> 00:11:55,380
Junior:
This is never gonna work.

245
00:11:55,382 --> 00:11:57,382
Trust me, angie would never
forget about the time

246
00:11:57,384 --> 00:11:59,417
We hid in the cement factory.

247
00:11:59,419 --> 00:12:00,819
No, I mean that
thing in there

248
00:12:00,821 --> 00:12:02,153
Is probably
already dead.

249
00:12:02,155 --> 00:12:03,254
Joe!

250
00:12:03,256 --> 00:12:04,389
Thank god.

251
00:12:06,258 --> 00:12:07,959
Junior: Don't take
another step.
Angie:
Junior, stop!

252
00:12:07,961 --> 00:12:09,461
No! This guy's a psychopath!

253
00:12:09,463 --> 00:12:11,496
James, I don't know what
your father told you,

254
00:12:11,498 --> 00:12:13,798
But barbie
didn't shoot me.

255
00:12:13,800 --> 00:12:16,468
A woman named maxine did.

256
00:12:16,470 --> 00:12:18,870
Maxine.

257
00:12:18,872 --> 00:12:20,472
My dad's friend?

258
00:12:22,308 --> 00:12:23,908
Barbie:
Hey.

259
00:12:23,910 --> 00:12:26,077
Is that supposed to do that?

260
00:12:29,381 --> 00:12:30,882
We have no idea

261
00:12:30,884 --> 00:12:32,050
Where joe and angie
are meeting.

262
00:12:32,052 --> 00:12:33,351
There's only so many
places to hide.

263
00:12:33,353 --> 00:12:35,053
We'll start with
the mcalisters' old barn.

264
00:12:35,055 --> 00:12:36,755
Phil:
Linda, you there?

265
00:12:36,757 --> 00:12:37,756
I'm sorry.

266
00:12:37,758 --> 00:12:38,890
Phil, are you
all right?

267
00:12:38,892 --> 00:12:40,225
Yeah, but barbie got away.

268
00:12:40,227 --> 00:12:41,226
What?

269
00:12:41,228 --> 00:12:42,327
He's with julia.

270
00:12:42,329 --> 00:12:43,361
She helped him escape.

271
00:12:43,363 --> 00:12:45,764
Phil, stay put.
I'm on my way.

272
00:12:45,766 --> 00:12:48,032
We ready?

273
00:12:48,034 --> 00:12:49,033
On three.

274
00:12:49,035 --> 00:12:51,102
One...

275
00:12:52,138 --> 00:12:54,506
Two...

276
00:12:56,442 --> 00:12:57,776
Three.

277
00:13:24,303 --> 00:13:26,204
Whoa.

278
00:13:31,076 --> 00:13:32,443
It opened up.

279
00:13:37,416 --> 00:13:39,450
Angie:
Oh, god.

280
00:13:45,224 --> 00:13:46,391
We're too late.

281
00:13:46,393 --> 00:13:48,493
It's dead.

282
00:13:55,534 --> 00:13:57,202
No...

283
00:13:57,204 --> 00:13:58,469
Look!

284
00:14:28,467 --> 00:14:30,535
♪

285
00:14:37,209 --> 00:14:39,577
Okay, is somebody gonna tell me
what the hell's going on here?

286
00:14:39,579 --> 00:14:41,646
I knew it.

287
00:14:42,648 --> 00:14:44,115
You're the monarch.

288
00:15:18,584 --> 00:15:19,951
Andrea...

289
00:15:19,953 --> 00:15:21,953
Andrea, what-what-what...
What's going on?

290
00:15:21,955 --> 00:15:23,655
Everyone's getting
right with the lord

291
00:15:23,657 --> 00:15:25,156
Before the end times.

292
00:15:25,158 --> 00:15:27,225
Hey, listen, I know
people are scared,

293
00:15:27,227 --> 00:15:28,092
But this is a,
this is a crisis,

294
00:15:28,094 --> 00:15:29,193
Not the damn apocalypse.

295
00:15:29,195 --> 00:15:32,230
"and I beheld
the sixth seal,

296
00:15:32,232 --> 00:15:36,000
The sun became black
as sackcloth."

297
00:15:36,002 --> 00:15:37,068
Andrea, listen...

298
00:15:37,070 --> 00:15:40,972
Just like revelations
said it would.

299
00:15:46,378 --> 00:15:48,413
Give us this day
our daily bread,

300
00:15:48,415 --> 00:15:50,315
And forgive us our trespasses...

301
00:15:52,319 --> 00:15:54,285
Please, god.

302
00:15:54,287 --> 00:15:57,221
Forgive us our trespasses,

303
00:15:57,223 --> 00:16:01,059
As we forgive those
who trespass against us.

304
00:16:01,061 --> 00:16:02,460
And lead us not

305
00:16:02,462 --> 00:16:05,263
Into temptation,
but deliver us from evil.

306
00:16:12,271 --> 00:16:14,339
Thank you, everybody,
for coming.

307
00:16:15,607 --> 00:16:18,376
I know there's been a bit of a
hole in our spiritual community

308
00:16:18,378 --> 00:16:20,478
Sine the passing
of reverend coggins,

309
00:16:20,480 --> 00:16:23,748
But I'm here
to tell you

310
00:16:23,750 --> 00:16:27,719
The good lord has not forgotten
about chester's mill.

311
00:16:27,721 --> 00:16:29,253
How can you
say that?

312
00:16:29,255 --> 00:16:32,223
But at least I could still
grow my crops.

313
00:16:33,994 --> 00:16:35,259
Without sunlight, we all starve.

314
00:16:37,029 --> 00:16:39,163
If we don't freeze
to death first.

315
00:16:39,165 --> 00:16:41,265
What if the temperature
starts dropping?

316
00:16:41,267 --> 00:16:42,567
My family is already

317
00:16:42,569 --> 00:16:44,202
Out of propane.
Listen,

318
00:16:44,204 --> 00:16:46,237
I give you my word: Nothing
like that's gonna happen.

319
00:16:46,239 --> 00:16:47,472
How do you know that?

320
00:16:59,119 --> 00:17:00,651
I don't.

321
00:17:07,159 --> 00:17:08,793
But I have faith.

322
00:17:10,396 --> 00:17:12,563
I have faith in us.

323
00:17:12,565 --> 00:17:14,399
I have faith in god.

324
00:17:14,401 --> 00:17:17,035
I have faith that he would never

325
00:17:17,037 --> 00:17:20,338
Ask more of us
than we can handle.

326
00:17:22,141 --> 00:17:23,574
The good book says,

327
00:17:23,576 --> 00:17:27,145
"light is sown
for the righteous."

328
00:17:27,147 --> 00:17:29,280
Well, there's been
too much evil

329
00:17:29,282 --> 00:17:31,616
And too much lawlessness
since that dome came down.

330
00:17:31,618 --> 00:17:33,117
Yep.
Man:
Yeah.

331
00:17:33,119 --> 00:17:34,152
Big jim:
That's about to change.

332
00:17:34,154 --> 00:17:37,221
And when it does...

333
00:17:37,223 --> 00:17:40,158
You trust me.

334
00:17:40,160 --> 00:17:42,727
Chester's mill will have
its new dawn.

335
00:17:46,465 --> 00:17:48,833
No way. I refuse to believe
<i>he's</i> the monarch.

336
00:17:48,835 --> 00:17:51,169
But this has to be the way
the dome picks a new leader.

337
00:17:51,171 --> 00:17:52,437
What,
by using insects?

338
00:17:52,439 --> 00:17:53,438
Norrie:
Uh-oh.

339
00:17:53,440 --> 00:17:54,839
What now?

340
00:17:54,841 --> 00:17:56,641
The egg.

341
00:17:56,643 --> 00:17:58,843
It's doing something.

342
00:17:58,845 --> 00:18:00,645
Is it gonna hatch?

343
00:18:05,517 --> 00:18:07,085
Looks more like
it's gonna explode.

344
00:18:14,627 --> 00:18:16,294
What is this?
What do we do?

345
00:18:16,296 --> 00:18:17,628
We get the hell away
from that thing!

346
00:18:17,630 --> 00:18:19,497
Barbie:
He's right, let's go!

347
00:18:20,866 --> 00:18:22,767
Wait.
Barbie:
No, julia,
the whole place

348
00:18:22,769 --> 00:18:24,302
Is about to come down on us.
Let's go!

349
00:18:28,173 --> 00:18:29,240
Angie:
Julia, don't touch it!

350
00:18:29,242 --> 00:18:30,575
It's dangerous!

351
00:18:49,561 --> 00:18:51,229
W...

352
00:18:51,231 --> 00:18:53,364
Why did the shaking stop?

353
00:19:08,547 --> 00:19:10,781
She's your monarch.

354
00:19:30,903 --> 00:19:32,904
Councilman rennie.

355
00:19:32,906 --> 00:19:36,707
Listen, I need you
to put together a work detail.

356
00:19:36,709 --> 00:19:38,676
Find as many carpenters
as you can.

357
00:19:38,678 --> 00:19:39,877
What is it?

358
00:19:39,879 --> 00:19:42,413
It's an idea
that came to me at church.

359
00:19:42,415 --> 00:19:44,282
My great-grandfather built
the last one

360
00:19:44,284 --> 00:19:45,516
That was in chester's mill.

361
00:19:53,292 --> 00:19:54,425
Are you serious?

362
00:19:54,427 --> 00:19:56,961
This town is on the brink
of chaos, son.

363
00:19:56,963 --> 00:19:58,763
If we want
to maintain the peace,

364
00:19:58,765 --> 00:20:01,432
We need to show everyone
exactly how serious we are

365
00:20:01,434 --> 00:20:02,800
About law and order.

366
00:20:04,469 --> 00:20:06,470
Phil:
All right.

367
00:20:07,439 --> 00:20:08,973
For dodee.

368
00:20:09,942 --> 00:20:11,943
Yes.

369
00:20:11,945 --> 00:20:14,212
For dodee.

370
00:20:29,962 --> 00:20:31,629
Jim, you there?

371
00:20:31,631 --> 00:20:33,864
Yeah, go ahead, linda.

372
00:20:33,866 --> 00:20:36,367
I'm at joe's,
but there's nothing here.

373
00:20:36,369 --> 00:20:38,236
You're sure?

374
00:20:38,238 --> 00:20:39,971
Any clues
to where they may have gone?

375
00:20:39,973 --> 00:20:44,609
Looks like they were using this
barn as some weird art project.

376
00:20:52,418 --> 00:20:56,554
Does "the pink stars
are falling in lines" mean?

377
00:21:05,797 --> 00:21:08,332
What did you say?

378
00:21:08,334 --> 00:21:10,868
"the pink stars
are falling in lines."

379
00:21:10,870 --> 00:21:13,537
Why? That mean something to you?

380
00:21:16,275 --> 00:21:18,676
Not for a long time.

381
00:21:21,046 --> 00:21:23,314
Meet me at my house, linda.

382
00:21:27,386 --> 00:21:30,521
So, if julia's
in charge now, then...

383
00:21:30,523 --> 00:21:32,757
What are we supposed to do next?

384
00:21:34,726 --> 00:21:38,062
I...

385
00:21:38,064 --> 00:21:39,730
I don't know.

386
00:21:39,732 --> 00:21:41,365
Exactly.

387
00:21:41,367 --> 00:21:43,000
She's not the monarch.
There's no such thing.

388
00:21:43,002 --> 00:21:44,835
We have to take that egg
to the real authorities.

389
00:21:44,837 --> 00:21:48,406
Angie:
No. We are not taking anything
to that monster.

390
00:21:48,408 --> 00:21:50,441
Don't talk like that.

391
00:21:50,443 --> 00:21:53,544
Barbie:
That's the truth,
junior.

392
00:21:53,546 --> 00:21:55,479
I watched your father
shoot maxine in the head.

393
00:21:55,481 --> 00:21:57,448
She was bound
and unarmed.

394
00:21:57,450 --> 00:21:59,550
He executed her.
Junior:
Bull.

395
00:21:59,552 --> 00:22:00,951
My dad? Hurt a woman?

396
00:22:00,953 --> 00:22:02,753
Angie:
Probably one
of the many reasons

397
00:22:02,755 --> 00:22:04,622
That the dome told us
to assassinate big jim.

398
00:22:04,624 --> 00:22:06,057
No, I'm-I'm done listening
to you all

399
00:22:06,059 --> 00:22:07,558
Run down my dad.

400
00:22:07,560 --> 00:22:09,660
He's the only thing keeping
this town together.

401
00:22:09,662 --> 00:22:11,562
James, calm...

402
00:22:11,564 --> 00:22:12,997
Shut up! All you do is lie!

403
00:22:12,999 --> 00:22:14,532
Junior...

404
00:22:14,534 --> 00:22:16,767
She told me in
these same tunnels.

405
00:22:16,769 --> 00:22:19,337
The only reason julia's even
in chester's mill is 'cause

406
00:22:19,339 --> 00:22:21,439
She got fired
from her last job for lying.

407
00:22:23,775 --> 00:22:26,911
Just like she's lying
about my dad right now.

408
00:22:34,553 --> 00:22:37,421
Hand it over, julia.

409
00:22:57,642 --> 00:22:58,609
Run!

410
00:22:59,511 --> 00:23:01,645
Angie, stop! Angie!

411
00:23:01,647 --> 00:23:02,646
Oh!

412
00:23:02,648 --> 00:23:03,547
Go!

413
00:23:06,852 --> 00:23:08,619
Barbie!

414
00:23:08,621 --> 00:23:09,653
Go!

415
00:23:15,560 --> 00:23:17,161
Get up.

416
00:23:17,163 --> 00:23:18,763
Get up!

417
00:23:19,831 --> 00:23:22,400
You're done.
You're done!

418
00:23:25,904 --> 00:23:28,539
Linda:
Jim, can you just tell me
what's going on?

419
00:23:28,541 --> 00:23:29,673
You wouldn't believe me,

420
00:23:29,675 --> 00:23:31,142
That's why
I have to show you.

421
00:23:31,144 --> 00:23:32,543
Show me what?

422
00:23:32,545 --> 00:23:35,546
My wife, pauline,
before she passed,

423
00:23:35,548 --> 00:23:37,047
She was paranoid, unstable,

424
00:23:37,049 --> 00:23:39,183
Ranting about all
kinds of crazy things.

425
00:23:39,185 --> 00:23:43,554
She kept saying one thing over
and over, like a mantra:

426
00:23:43,556 --> 00:23:46,590
"the pink stars are falling."

427
00:23:46,592 --> 00:23:48,726
Are you sure?

428
00:23:48,728 --> 00:23:52,496
Maybe it's a coincidence.

429
00:24:05,144 --> 00:24:07,611
Oh, thank god.

430
00:24:07,613 --> 00:24:08,646
Are you okay?

431
00:24:08,648 --> 00:24:10,614
Yeah. How about the others?

432
00:24:10,616 --> 00:24:11,582
Julia:
Junior got barbie.

433
00:24:11,584 --> 00:24:13,517
What are we gonna do now?

434
00:24:14,786 --> 00:24:17,888
Okay, something
this powerful has got

435
00:24:17,890 --> 00:24:20,024
To be what's generating
the big dome.

436
00:24:20,026 --> 00:24:22,660
If we destroy the egg,
maybe it'll go away.

437
00:24:22,662 --> 00:24:24,161
Or maybe it'll start
another earthquake.

438
00:24:24,163 --> 00:24:25,729
Why don't we just try asking it?

439
00:24:35,540 --> 00:24:37,842
What do I say?

440
00:24:39,644 --> 00:24:41,111
Whatever feels right.

441
00:24:46,718 --> 00:24:48,853
Please...

442
00:24:50,655 --> 00:24:52,990
Just tell us what to do.

443
00:24:58,864 --> 00:25:01,732
Great. Can we try
blowing it up now?

444
00:25:01,734 --> 00:25:04,235
Holy...

445
00:25:12,644 --> 00:25:14,812
Mom?

446
00:25:25,857 --> 00:25:28,192
So, she knew all this
was gonna happen.

447
00:25:28,194 --> 00:25:29,260
How is that possible?

448
00:25:29,262 --> 00:25:31,595
I don't know.

449
00:25:31,597 --> 00:25:35,266
But the whole time we kept
thinking she was sick...

450
00:25:35,268 --> 00:25:37,835
Maybe she was trying to warn us.

451
00:25:39,938 --> 00:25:42,573
I don't know why
I didn't see it.

452
00:25:43,208 --> 00:25:45,676
Maybe I could have done
more for her.

453
00:25:45,678 --> 00:25:48,612
Jim, you need
to stay strong... For us.

454
00:25:48,614 --> 00:25:52,149
I mean, if your wife saw
the dome coming,

455
00:25:52,151 --> 00:25:55,052
That means
your family's important.

456
00:25:55,054 --> 00:25:57,221
It means <i>you're</i> important.

457
00:25:59,958 --> 00:26:01,325
Linda, it's junior.

458
00:26:02,260 --> 00:26:03,861
Where the hell
have you been?

459
00:26:03,863 --> 00:26:07,264
I've got barbie in custody.
I'm bringing him in.

460
00:26:09,701 --> 00:26:11,201
Mom...
Sweetheart...

461
00:26:12,704 --> 00:26:14,838
I don't think
that's your mother.

462
00:26:22,180 --> 00:26:23,247
Forgive us,

463
00:26:23,249 --> 00:26:27,952
We're still learning
to speak with you.

464
00:26:27,954 --> 00:26:29,753
We've taken on
a familiar appearance

465
00:26:29,755 --> 00:26:31,822
To help bridge the divide.

466
00:26:33,091 --> 00:26:35,159
What divide?

467
00:26:37,195 --> 00:26:39,096
What the hell are you?

468
00:26:41,933 --> 00:26:43,634
Joe:
I think,

469
00:26:43,636 --> 00:26:48,205
I think it's whoever sent
the dome to chester's mill.

470
00:26:56,748 --> 00:26:58,115
Angie:
Why?

471
00:26:59,651 --> 00:27:01,819
Why are you punishing us?

472
00:27:01,821 --> 00:27:05,689
The dome wasn't sent
to punish you.

473
00:27:05,691 --> 00:27:07,958
It was sent to protect you.

474
00:27:09,894 --> 00:27:11,996
Protect us from what?

475
00:27:13,331 --> 00:27:16,333
You'll see... In time.

476
00:27:16,335 --> 00:27:17,768
How can we see
anything

477
00:27:17,770 --> 00:27:20,037
Now that you've
blacked out the dome?

478
00:27:20,039 --> 00:27:24,675
If you want
the darkness to abate,

479
00:27:24,677 --> 00:27:26,710
You must earn the light.

480
00:27:28,146 --> 00:27:29,747
How?

481
00:27:29,749 --> 00:27:31,849
By protecting the egg.

482
00:27:36,221 --> 00:27:37,988
And if we fail,

483
00:27:37,990 --> 00:27:40,924
It's the end, isn't it?

484
00:27:40,926 --> 00:27:43,260
For all of us.

485
00:27:53,138 --> 00:27:57,141
So how do we protect it?

486
00:27:57,143 --> 00:27:59,009
Who are we protecting it from?

487
00:28:07,820 --> 00:28:09,953
Oh, no.

488
00:28:29,275 --> 00:28:31,975
You're on the wrong side
of things here.

489
00:28:31,977 --> 00:28:33,410
Shut up.

490
00:28:54,466 --> 00:28:56,734
Welcome back.

491
00:28:59,237 --> 00:29:02,106
This egg--
tell me where they took it.

492
00:29:04,342 --> 00:29:07,044
It's the key to
all this, isn't it?

493
00:29:09,080 --> 00:29:11,081
Making the darkness go away?

494
00:29:11,083 --> 00:29:13,150
Controlling the dome?

495
00:29:16,087 --> 00:29:18,155
You want to know a secret?

496
00:29:24,529 --> 00:29:28,232
You may think that you're some
kind of god to these people.

497
00:29:29,801 --> 00:29:32,236
But I think we both know
what you really are.

498
00:29:32,238 --> 00:29:36,807
What's that, a... Criminal?

499
00:29:37,776 --> 00:29:40,043
Worse.

500
00:29:41,012 --> 00:29:43,080
A politician.

501
00:29:50,289 --> 00:29:52,289
Okay, we're clear.

502
00:29:52,291 --> 00:29:53,891
Go to the back room.

503
00:29:53,893 --> 00:29:55,392
Stay away from the windows.

504
00:29:59,831 --> 00:30:02,299
Were those gallows going up
next to town hall?

505
00:30:02,301 --> 00:30:04,434
This day just
keeps getting awesomer.

506
00:30:04,436 --> 00:30:06,370
What do we do about the egg?

507
00:30:06,372 --> 00:30:07,838
We need to hide it
someplace safe.

508
00:30:07,840 --> 00:30:09,206
We're all stuck
in the same podunk town.

509
00:30:09,208 --> 00:30:10,374
There's nowhere
to stash anything.

510
00:30:10,376 --> 00:30:12,342
This is big jim rennie
with a message

511
00:30:12,344 --> 00:30:14,278
For julia shumway.

512
00:30:14,280 --> 00:30:17,014
We know you have a dangerous
weapon in your possession.

513
00:30:17,016 --> 00:30:20,450
Bring it to us now,
and we'll discuss

514
00:30:20,452 --> 00:30:23,921
A reduced sentence for
your accomplice, dale barbara.

515
00:30:23,923 --> 00:30:27,191
But fail to comply
within the hour...

516
00:30:27,193 --> 00:30:31,395
And barbie pays the ultimate
price for his crime.

517
00:30:50,415 --> 00:30:52,449
Dad.

518
00:30:52,451 --> 00:30:54,518
Junior.

519
00:30:54,520 --> 00:30:56,920
Hey, good work with barbie.

520
00:30:56,922 --> 00:30:58,188
He and his crew...

521
00:30:58,190 --> 00:31:00,591
They want to assassinate you.

522
00:31:00,593 --> 00:31:02,492
What are you talking about?

523
00:31:02,494 --> 00:31:04,361
They say that you're dangerous,

524
00:31:04,363 --> 00:31:06,430
That you murdered people.

525
00:31:09,868 --> 00:31:12,169
Do you believe it?

526
00:31:13,872 --> 00:31:15,939
Should I?

527
00:31:20,111 --> 00:31:22,179
You know, son,

528
00:31:22,181 --> 00:31:24,648
Before today, I-I...

529
00:31:24,650 --> 00:31:28,285
Never put much stock
in miracles.

530
00:31:34,025 --> 00:31:35,959
I went to see
your mom's old studio

531
00:31:35,961 --> 00:31:38,362
This afternoon.

532
00:31:38,364 --> 00:31:40,130
Haven't set
foot in there

533
00:31:40,132 --> 00:31:42,199
Since the day she passed.

534
00:31:44,369 --> 00:31:46,270
You saw them?

535
00:31:46,272 --> 00:31:48,472
The paintings?

536
00:31:49,674 --> 00:31:51,675
That this dome--

537
00:31:51,677 --> 00:31:54,544
It wasn't some accident.

538
00:31:55,914 --> 00:31:58,081
It was destiny.

539
00:31:59,183 --> 00:32:01,251
<i>Our</i> destiny.

540
00:32:02,220 --> 00:32:04,054
I don't understand.

541
00:32:04,056 --> 00:32:07,524
There's nothing
a good man won't do

542
00:32:07,526 --> 00:32:09,259
For the people
he loves.

543
00:32:09,261 --> 00:32:13,330
That's what your mom used
to say all the time, right?

544
00:32:14,299 --> 00:32:18,001
You want the truth?

545
00:32:21,940 --> 00:32:24,241
I <i>have</i> taken lives.

546
00:32:27,445 --> 00:32:30,948
But none that didn't absolutely

547
00:32:30,950 --> 00:32:34,351
Need to be taken...

548
00:32:34,353 --> 00:32:36,586
For the good of this town.

549
00:32:38,022 --> 00:32:40,624
Then why didn't you tell me?

550
00:32:40,626 --> 00:32:43,994
Because I thought I needed
to protect you from all this.

551
00:32:43,996 --> 00:32:45,429
But I realize now

552
00:32:45,431 --> 00:32:47,664
That was a
mistake.

553
00:32:49,067 --> 00:32:51,068
You and I...

554
00:32:51,070 --> 00:32:53,437
Are in this together.

555
00:32:54,572 --> 00:32:57,240
The rennies.

556
00:32:57,242 --> 00:32:59,309
We were chosen.

557
00:33:01,112 --> 00:33:03,113
Your mother knew it,

558
00:33:03,115 --> 00:33:06,316
And she was trying with
all her heart to tell us.

559
00:33:06,318 --> 00:33:08,685
Those pink stars
she painted

560
00:33:08,687 --> 00:33:11,021
Are a message, son.

561
00:33:13,291 --> 00:33:16,093
And they're shining down on you.

562
00:33:22,400 --> 00:33:24,401
You and I need to do

563
00:33:24,403 --> 00:33:27,037
What nobody else
in chester's mill can.

564
00:33:27,039 --> 00:33:29,439
We need to make
the hard decisions,

565
00:33:29,441 --> 00:33:31,508
Act on 'em, and lead.

566
00:33:33,578 --> 00:33:35,645
And from here on out...

567
00:33:38,216 --> 00:33:40,283
...No more secrets between us.

568
00:34:02,340 --> 00:34:04,341
We have to
help him.

569
00:34:04,343 --> 00:34:07,544
Norrie:
But we can't just
give big jim the egg.

570
00:34:07,546 --> 00:34:11,481
My mom, or... That woman said
it would be the end for all

571
00:34:11,483 --> 00:34:13,083
Of us if we didn't
protect that thing.

572
00:34:13,085 --> 00:34:14,251
What does that
even mean?

573
00:34:14,253 --> 00:34:15,685
It means our whole town
is as good as dead

574
00:34:15,687 --> 00:34:17,454
If we let this fall
into the wrong hands.

575
00:34:17,456 --> 00:34:19,356
Norrie:
Doesn't get more wrong
than big jim.

576
00:34:19,358 --> 00:34:21,058
Dome told us as much.

577
00:34:21,060 --> 00:34:22,692
Joe:
How do we protect
chester's mill

578
00:34:22,694 --> 00:34:24,761
<i>And</i> save barbie?

579
00:34:27,665 --> 00:34:30,400
We can't.

580
00:34:30,402 --> 00:34:33,236
So, what the hell do we do?

581
00:34:33,238 --> 00:34:35,639
We don't do anything.

582
00:34:37,241 --> 00:34:40,377
If I'm really the monarch,
this has to be my decision.

583
00:34:40,379 --> 00:34:42,179
You three have done enough.

584
00:34:42,181 --> 00:34:44,214
I want you
to go get somewhere safe.

585
00:34:44,216 --> 00:34:46,216
What are you gonna do?

586
00:35:54,318 --> 00:35:57,154
Big jim:
I know you're scared.

587
00:35:57,156 --> 00:36:00,423
I'm scared, too.

588
00:36:00,425 --> 00:36:03,293
From the very first day
this dome appeared,

589
00:36:03,295 --> 00:36:05,462
Elements from outside

590
00:36:05,464 --> 00:36:08,198
Our fair town have attempted to

591
00:36:08,200 --> 00:36:10,300
Sow the seeds of fear and hatred

592
00:36:10,302 --> 00:36:12,335
In an effort to divide us.

593
00:36:12,337 --> 00:36:15,205
Well, no more.

594
00:36:15,207 --> 00:36:18,742
Today, chester's mill

595
00:36:18,744 --> 00:36:21,411
Sentences dale
barbara to death.

596
00:36:50,441 --> 00:36:52,909
♪

597
00:38:30,408 --> 00:38:32,575
Big jim:
Friends, clearly

598
00:38:32,577 --> 00:38:35,679
The good lord has looked upon
our work here today with favor.

599
00:38:35,681 --> 00:38:37,747
Let us thank him
for this blessing.

600
00:39:15,519 --> 00:39:17,520
Dad, what's happening?

601
00:39:17,522 --> 00:39:18,755
Now, son.

602
00:39:18,757 --> 00:39:20,790
Do it now!

603
00:39:23,527 --> 00:39:24,761
Now, junior!

604
00:39:24,763 --> 00:39:26,730
Do it now!

605
